Here are several ways to create a good-looking button using HTML and CSS:

1. Basic Modern Button:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        .btn {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            border: none;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px 32px;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: inline-block;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin: 4px 2px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 8px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <button class="btn">Click Me</button>
</body>
</html>
```

2. Gradient Button:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        .gradient-btn {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #ff7e5f, #feb47b);
            border: none;
            color: white;
            padding: 15px 32px;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: inline-block;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin: 4px 2px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 50px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .gradient-btn:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <button class="gradient-btn">Submit</button>
</body>
</html>
```

